('cORZ1585401787pMIj', 'file-manager/thumbnail_Image.jpg', '2017 Blank Canvas \'ELEMENT\' Syrah', '2017 Blank Canvas \'ELEMENT\' Syrah', '94 POINTS Cameron Douglas MS | 92 POINTS Robert Parker Wine Advocate', '94 POINTS Cameron Douglas MS | 92 POINTS Robert Parker Wine Advocate', 2, 'Syrah, NZ', '', '2020-03-28', '2021-03-29', '<p><span style=\"color: #323130; font-family: \'Segoe UI\', \'Segoe UI Web (West European)\', \'Segoe UI\', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Blank Canvas \'ELEMENT\' Syrah from Gimblett Gravels, Hawkes Bay.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #323130; font-family: \'Segoe UI\', \'Segoe UI Web (West European)\', \'Segoe UI\', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">A classic look of cool-climate-Syrah, &nbsp;very fragrant, it gives nose of blueberries, dried violets, dried rose, peppercorns and pencil shavings. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #323130; font-family: \'Segoe UI\', \'Segoe UI Web (West European)\', \'Segoe UI\', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">On the palate, the fine-grain tannins, and a lovely and balanced acidity, both contribute to a nice texture: layers of complexity in flavours of spicy, peppery and savoury. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #323130; font-family: \'Segoe UI\', \'Segoe UI Web (West European)\', \'Segoe UI\', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Also can see a huge potential to be aged longer.</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"color: #323130; font-family: \'Segoe UI\', \'Segoe UI Web (West European)\', \'Segoe UI\', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Blank Canvas \'ELEMENT\' Syrah from Gimblett Gravels, Hawkes Bay.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #323130; font-family: \'Segoe UI\', \'Segoe UI Web (West European)\', \'Segoe UI\', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">A classic look of cool-climate-Syrah, &nbsp;very fragrant, it gives nose of blueberries, dried violets, dried rose, peppercorns and pencil shavings.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #323130; font-family: \'Segoe UI\', \'Segoe UI Web (West European)\', \'Segoe UI\', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">On the palate, the fine-grain tannins, and a lovely and balanced acidity, both contribute to a nice texture: layers of complexity in flavours of spicy, peppery and savoury.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #323130; font-family: \'Segoe UI\', \'Segoe UI Web (West European)\', \'Segoe UI\', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Also can see a huge potential to be aged longer.</span></p>', 1, 1, 0, 1, 1, 45, '2020-03-28 21:23:07', '2021-01-11 14:11:40'),
('ImKw1603766207WAkA', 'file-manager/WeChat Image_20201027152843.jpg', 'The Wine Cave Wine Club Article - Vol.1: Te Kano Estate', 'The Wine Cave Wine Club Article - Vol.1: Te Kano Estate', '‘Te Kano’ means ‘the seed’ in Maori, the name celebrates a prehistoric plant called Kowhai tree affectionately known as ‘Old Man Kowhai’ on the Northburn slopes above Lake Dunstan where Te Kano Estate is located.', '‘Te Kano’ means ‘the seed’ in Maori, the name celebrates a prehistoric plant called Kowhai tree affectionately known as ‘Old Man Kowhai’ on the Northburn slopes above Lake Dunstan where Te Kano Estate is located.', 2, 'nzwine, tasting notes', 'nzwine, tasting notes', '2020-10-27', '2024-12-28', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Hello, The Wine Cave Wine Club members. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">My Name is Jamie Yuanzhe Li, the store manager of The Wine Cave, and a WSET Diploma student that enjoys wine, spirits, beer, sake and food and won&rsquo;t stop talking about those.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">My main job at The Wine Cave is always to find the next bottle of beautiful poetry&hellip;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">From this week, I will post a blog with a tasting review of one bottle or one brand with a few bottles every week. I hope this can help you confidently make a decision on the purchase of your next bottle.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">This week, I&rsquo;m bringing you a brand --- Te Kano Estate, and the ranges.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">&lsquo;Te Kano&rsquo; means &lsquo;the seed&rsquo; in Maori, the name celebrates a prehistoric plant called Kowhai tree affectionately known as &lsquo;Old Man Kowhai&rsquo; on the Northburn slopes above Lake Dunstan where Te Kano Estate is located. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Te Kano Estate comprises three vineyards, Northburn, &lsquo;Jerome&rsquo; in Bannockburn and &lsquo;Eliza&rsquo; in Bannockburn. Te Kano Estate is always after the very best expression of site and climate which is called &lsquo;Terroir&rsquo;. A hand selection from vineyards and barrels is a must as what they emphasize is always the Quality, not the Quantity. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-char-indent-count: 0; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-NZ\" style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">1.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><a href=\"http://shopwinecave.nz/wine/ebGS1603768253evPm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Blanc de Noir 2018</span></a></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">A fresh, clean and mineral wine made from 100% Pinot Noir. Hand-picked grapes, from The Eliza vineyard on Felton Road, were delicately whole bunch pressed by a long and gentle pressure to minimize the skin contact. Then the juice experienced a very cool and long fermentation in stainless steel so that the wine can be with delicate aromatics and elegant structure.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">The nose is with a very delicate white strawberry, white cherry and peach nose. The acidity is bright and clean, the wine shows more white fruits and white flowers on palate, meanwhile it brings some salty and spicy notes with a long mineral finish.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">BTW, I enjoyed this wine very well with a misoyaki salmon dish.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-char-indent-count: 0; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-NZ\" style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">2.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><a href=\"http://shopwinecave.nz/wine/ISFI1603768776zkBN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Pinot Gris 2019</span></a></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">100% hand-harvested from Jerome vineyard and whole bunch pressed. A long, cool fermentation in stainless steel was applied to preserve freshness and aromatics, with lees contact post-fermentation to build mid palate texture.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Layers of aromas of pear, white peach, honeysuckle, and flint. Those nose characteristics continue onto the palate with more juicy peach, green apple and some white pepper. The fine boned acidity is nicely balanced with a mild texture leading to a crisp and dry finish.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-char-indent-count: 0; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-NZ\" style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">3.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><a href=\"http://shopwinecave.nz/wine/gPoB1603768501bjXr\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Chardonnay 2019</span></a></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Carefully selected and hand-harvested fruit from Jerome vineyard. Whole bunch pressed to French oak barrels for fermentation for 10 months. then Malolactic fermentation was applied partially. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">This Chardonnay has surprised me because it does not only show the elegant aromas of white peach, citrus and flint which are iconic style of the &lsquo;Cental Chardonnay&rsquo;, but on the palate, it also gives concentrated flavours of ripe peach, nectarine and pineapple fellow by biscuit, toasty oak and roasted almonds. Meanwhile the beautiful and lingering acidity adds balance and minerality. The finish is also long and mineral. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-char-indent-count: 0; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-NZ\" style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">4.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><a href=\"http://shopwinecave.nz/wine/uWWd1603768908CewY\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Pinot Noir 2017</span></a></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Handpicked Pinot Noir grapes, from both Eliza and Jerome vineyard, were destemmed in separate batches, with a 15% wholebunch component used to add complexity and structure. Fermentation with indigenous yeast was following by 12 months of maturation in new and older French oak barriques.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">When we normally talk about &lsquo;Central Pinot&rsquo;, fruity is the most used adjective. But a good &lsquo;Central Pinot&rsquo; cannot be only with fruitiness! This &lsquo;Central Pinot&rsquo; is with supple and complex aromas of spices, toffee, mocha and dark berry fruits. On the palate, the fruitiness is ripe and juicy. But there are more savoury notes of spices, earth, and meats, combined with a fine-grained tannin, which create a wine with a beautiful depth. The finish is fully dark-berry-juicy and warm spicy. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Personally, I&rsquo;m into the Chardonnay and Pinot Noir very much, but the Blanc de Noir is a very interesting wine that deserves to have a try and to put in your Vivino. There has been a debate about the Blanc de Noir, is this wine a Rose or not? Well, it can be called a Rose when we are looking at the variety and winemaking method. But the reason why I don&rsquo;t call it a Rose is because the aroma and flavour characteristics are totally different. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Thank you for your view of this blog article. If you would like to have any of those wine, please see the product links by clicking the product names above.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\">&nbsp;</p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Hello, The Wine Cave Wine Club members.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">My Name is Jamie Yuanzhe Li, the store manager of The Wine Cave, and a WSET Diploma student that enjoys wine, spirits, beer, sake and food and won&rsquo;t stop talking about those.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">My main job at The Wine Cave is always to find the next bottle of beautiful poetry&hellip;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">From this week, I will post a blog with a tasting review of one bottle or one brand with a few bottles every week. I hope this can help you confidently make a decision on the purchase of your next bottle.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">This week, I&rsquo;m bringing you a brand --- Te Kano Estate, and the ranges.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">&lsquo;Te Kano&rsquo; means &lsquo;the seed&rsquo; in Maori, the name celebrates a prehistoric plant called Kowhai tree affectionately known as &lsquo;Old Man Kowhai&rsquo; on the Northburn slopes above Lake Dunstan where Te Kano Estate is located.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Te Kano Estate comprises three vineyards, Northburn, &lsquo;Jerome&rsquo; in Bannockburn and &lsquo;Eliza&rsquo; in Bannockburn. Te Kano Estate is always after the very best expression of site and climate which is called &lsquo;Terroir&rsquo;. A hand selection from vineyards and barrels is a must as what they emphasize is always the Quality, not the Quantity.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-char-indent-count: 0; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">1.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><a href=\"http://shopwinecave.nz/wine/ebGS1603768253evPm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Blanc de Noir 2018</span></a></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">A fresh, clean and mineral wine made from 100% Pinot Noir. Hand-picked grapes, from The Eliza vineyard on Felton Road, were delicately whole bunch pressed by a long and gentle pressure to minimize the skin contact. Then the juice experienced a very cool and long fermentation in stainless steel so that the wine can be with delicate aromatics and elegant structure.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">The nose is with a very delicate white strawberry, white cherry and peach nose. The acidity is bright and clean, the wine shows more white fruits and white flowers on palate, meanwhile it brings some salty and spicy notes with a long mineral finish.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">BTW, I enjoyed this wine very well with a misoyaki salmon dish.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-char-indent-count: 0; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">2.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><a href=\"http://shopwinecave.nz/wine/ISFI1603768776zkBN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Pinot Gris 2019</span></a></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">100% hand-harvested from Jerome vineyard and whole bunch pressed. A long, cool fermentation in stainless steel was applied to preserve freshness and aromatics, with lees contact post-fermentation to build mid palate texture.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Layers of aromas of pear, white peach, honeysuckle, and flint. Those nose characteristics continue onto the palate with more juicy peach, green apple and some white pepper. The fine boned acidity is nicely balanced with a mild texture leading to a crisp and dry finish.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-char-indent-count: 0; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">3.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><a href=\"http://shopwinecave.nz/wine/gPoB1603768501bjXr\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Chardonnay 2019</span></a></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Carefully selected and hand-harvested fruit from Jerome vineyard. Whole bunch pressed to French oak barrels for fermentation for 10 months. then Malolactic fermentation was applied partially.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">This Chardonnay has surprised me because it does not only show the elegant aromas of white peach, citrus and flint which are iconic style of the &lsquo;Cental Chardonnay&rsquo;, but on the palate, it also gives concentrated flavours of ripe peach, nectarine and pineapple fellow by biscuit, toasty oak and roasted almonds. Meanwhile the beautiful and lingering acidity adds balance and minerality. The finish is also long and mineral.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-char-indent-count: 0; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">4.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><a href=\"http://shopwinecave.nz/wine/uWWd1603768908CewY\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Pinot Noir 2017</span></a></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Handpicked Pinot Noir grapes, from both Eliza and Jerome vineyard, were destemmed in separate batches, with a 15% wholebunch component used to add complexity and structure. Fermentation with indigenous yeast was following by 12 months of maturation in new and older French oak barriques.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">When we normally talk about &lsquo;Central Pinot&rsquo;, fruity is the most used adjective. But a good &lsquo;Central Pinot&rsquo; cannot be only with fruitiness! This &lsquo;Central Pinot&rsquo; is with supple and complex aromas of spices, toffee, mocha and dark berry fruits. On the palate, the fruitiness is ripe and juicy. But there are more savoury notes of spices, earth, and meats, combined with a fine-grained tannin, which create a wine with a beautiful depth. The finish is fully dark-berry-juicy and warm spicy.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt; text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Personally, I&rsquo;m into the Chardonnay and Pinot Noir very much, but the Blanc de Noir is a very interesting wine that deserves to have a try and to put in your Vivino. There has been a debate about the Blanc de Noir, is this wine a Rose or not? Well, it can be called a Rose when we are looking at the variety and winemaking method. But the reason why I don&rsquo;t call it a Rose is because the aroma and flavour characteristics are totally different.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Thank you for your view of this blog article. If you would like to have any of those wine, please see the product links by clicking the product names above.</span></p>', 1, 1, 0, 1, 1, 95, '2020-10-27 10:36:47', '2021-01-12 19:42:33'),
('oPVf1583058085yVFJ', '', '文章1', 'Article', 'Now our tastings are over for the year, it is time to say a fond farewell to the hearty and home-cooked fare that has so often been served up during these evenings by John and Richard’s parents, Maurice and Mary-Jane Caro. It has come time for them to permanently retire from the responsibility that has consumed their retirement every few weeks, for so many years. From rich tagines to slow-cooked ragouts, these meals required days in their home kitchen to prepare – especially at such scale! – and', 'Now our tastings are over for the year, it is time to say a fond farewell to the hearty and home-cooked fare that has so often been served up during these evenings by John and Richard’s parents, Maurice and Mary-Jane Caro. It has come time for them to permanently retire from the responsibility that has consumed their retirement every few weeks, for so many years. From rich tagines to slow-cooked ragouts, these meals required days in their home kitchen to prepare – especially at such scale! – and', 2, 'tag1,tag2', '標籤1,標籤2', '2020-03-01', '2020-03-31', '<p>test</p>', '<p>en test</p>', 1, 1, 0, 1, 1, 7, '2020-03-01 18:21:25', '2020-03-28 21:09:19'),
('stXW1604566757zDqg', 'file-manager/unnamed.jpg', 'THE WINE CAVE WINE CLUB ARTICLE - VOL.2: Radburnd Hawkes Bay Chardonnay', 'THE WINE CAVE WINE CLUB ARTICLE - VOL.2: Radburnd Hawkes Bay Chardonnay', 'Radburnd Cellars was established in 2017, with the single purpose of Kate Radburnd making her very best wine from each vintage using the best fruits. So, production is very limited.', 'Radburnd Cellars was established in 2017, with the single purpose of Kate Radburnd making her very best wine from each vintage using the best fruits. So, production is very limited.', 2, 'nzwine, tasting notes', 'nzwine, tasting notes', '2020-11-05', '2022-11-06', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Hello, The Wine Cave Wine Club members. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">My Name is Jamie Yuanzhe Li, the store manager of The Wine Cave, and a WSET Diploma student that enjoys wine, spirits, beer, sake and food and won&rsquo;t stop talking about those.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">My main job at The Wine Cave is always to find the next bottle of beautiful poetry&hellip;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">From this week, I will post a blog with a tasting review of one bottle or one brand with a few bottles every week. I hope this can help you confidently make a decision on purchase of your next bottle.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">This week, I&rsquo;m bringing you a wine --- Radburnd Cellars Chardonnay</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Radburnd Cellars was established in 2017, with the single purpose of Kate Radburnd making her very best wine from each vintage using the best fruits. So, the production is very limited.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">The lady behind the brand, is one of NZ&rsquo;s most highly respected winemakers, Kate Radburnd. She has been making wine for more than 35 years in Hawkes&rsquo; Bay. Kate has been a Director of New Zealand Winegrowers, Deputy Chair of the Council of the Eastern Institute of Technology in Hawke\'s Bay, and a wine consultant to Air New Zealand. She pioneered the introduction of the winery programme for Sustainable Wine Growing New Zealand.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">In recognition of her services to New Zealand wine, Kate was awarded the Sir George Fistonich medal in 2010 and was made a Fellow of New Zealand Winegrowers in 2015, the first female winemaker to receive the award. In 2019, Kate was inducted into the New Zealand Wine Hall of Fame.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Now she&rsquo;s back doing the wine she loves most, in the way she wants, and with her best care. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\"><a href=\"http://shopwinecave.nz/wine/ukLd1604555680leGt\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Radburnd Hawkes Bay Chardonnay 2018</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">The fruits were sourced from two sites in Hawke&rsquo;s Bay: Mangatahi and Bridge Pa. The Mangatahi site is inland and elevated and later ripening, while Bridge Pa ripens Chardonnay beautifully with their red metal soils, the combination helpfully makes sure the balance of the wine.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">&ldquo;This Chardonnay was hand-harvested and cooled overnight. </span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">The cooled bunches were hand-sorted then whole bunched pressed. The majority of juice was cold settled then racked to barrel. Fermentation was in new and seasoned French oak, with selected cultured yeast and indigenous yeast, for added complexity. A combination of 500L puncheons and 225L barriques were employed. Lees stirring post-fermentation was regular and malolactic fermentation was completed in barrel. The Chardonnay matured in barrel for 9 months before blending and bottling.&rdquo; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">An elegant and refined Chardonnay carrying beautiful citrus, red apple and fresh nutty noses. On the palate, the mouthful and refined texture are balanced by bright acidity. When I first time opened a bottle, in March, I was impressed by the clean freshness and the delicacy.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">Then I enjoyed the second bottle with Jen from Radburnd Cellars last week (in October). The wine has evolved over the 7 months, it has developed beautifully with more and more white dried fruits, dried flowers and roasted almond. And I trust it will develop better in the future 5-7 years.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\"><span style=\"color: #808080; font-family: open_sansregular, \'Helvetica Neue\', Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14.4px;\">Thank you for your view of this blog article. If you would like to have any of those wine, please see the product links by clicking the product names above</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm; mso-char-indent-count: 0;\">&nbsp;</p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Hello, The Wine Cave Wine Club members.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">My Name is Jamie Yuanzhe Li, the store manager of The Wine Cave, and a WSET Diploma student that enjoys wine, spirits, beer, sake and food and won&rsquo;t stop talking about those.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">My main job at The Wine Cave is always to find the next bottle of beautiful poetry&hellip;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">From this week, I will post a blog with a tasting review of one bottle or one brand with a few bottles every week. I hope this can help you confidently make a decision on purchase of your next bottle.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">This week, I&rsquo;m bringing you a wine --- Radburnd Cellars Chardonnay</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Radburnd Cellars was established in 2017, with the single purpose of Kate Radburnd making her very best wine from each vintage using the best fruits. So, the production is very limited.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">The lady behind the brand, is one of NZ&rsquo;s most highly respected winemakers, Kate Radburnd. She has been making wine for more than 35 years in Hawkes&rsquo; Bay. Kate has been a Director of New Zealand Winegrowers, Deputy Chair of the Council of the Eastern Institute of Technology in Hawke\'s Bay, and a wine consultant to Air New Zealand. She pioneered the introduction of the winery programme for Sustainable Wine Growing New Zealand.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">In recognition of her services to New Zealand wine, Kate was awarded the Sir George Fistonich medal in 2010 and was made a Fellow of New Zealand Winegrowers in 2015, the first female winemaker to receive the award. In 2019, Kate was inducted into the New Zealand Wine Hall of Fame.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Now she&rsquo;s back doing the wine she loves most, in the way she wants, and with her best care.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><a href=\"http://shopwinecave.nz/wine/ukLd1604555680leGt\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Radburnd Hawkes Bay Chardonnay 2018</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">The fruits were sourced from two sites in Hawke&rsquo;s Bay: Mangatahi and Bridge Pa. The Mangatahi site is inland and elevated and later ripening, while Bridge Pa ripens Chardonnay beautifully with their red metal soils, the combination helpfully makes sure the balance of the wine.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">&ldquo;This Chardonnay was hand-harvested and cooled overnight.&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">The cooled bunches were hand-sorted then whole bunched pressed. The majority of juice was cold settled then racked to barrel. Fermentation was in new and seasoned French oak, with selected cultured yeast and indigenous yeast, for added complexity. A combination of 500L puncheons and 225L barriques were employed. Lees stirring post-fermentation was regular and malolactic fermentation was completed in barrel. The Chardonnay matured in barrel for 9 months before blending and bottling.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">An elegant and refined Chardonnay carrying beautiful citrus, red apple and fresh nutty noses. On the palate, the mouthful and refined texture are balanced by bright acidity. When I first time opened a bottle, in March, I was impressed by the clean freshness and the delicacy.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Then I enjoyed the second bottle with Jen from Radburnd Cellars last week (in October). The wine has evolved over the 7 months, it has developed beautifully with more and more white dried fruits, dried flowers and roasted almond. And I trust it will develop better in the future 5-7 years.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"color: #808080; font-family: open_sansregular, \'Helvetica Neue\', Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14.4px;\">Thank you for your view of this blog article. If you would like to have any of those wine, please see the product links by clicking the product names above</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: 0cm;\">&nbsp;</p>', 1, 1, 0, 1, 1, 26, '2020-11-05 16:59:17', '2020-12-22 14:03:19');

