('lGfo1582730670VQqX', 'file-manager/wine/替换图/bordeaux-chateau-couronneau-le-fougueux-sans-souffre-ajoute-2017.png', '', '', 'Chateau Couronneau Le Fougueux 2017', '', 32, '', 750, 15, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'FR', 11, 2, '[\"8\",\"9\"]', NULL, NULL, 3, '2020-02-26', '2021-02-26', 0, 17, 1, 0, 0, 'Dark, spicy and fleshy. Nothing of the brittle charm of other wines without sulphur additive, but very juicy with a long finish. Immensely concentrated, with impressive plum and cherry fruit and solid structure. Matches dark meat and spicy sauces\r\nNo sulphites were added in the vineyard or in the cellar.', '<p><span style=\"color: #606060; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Originally established way back in the 15th century, the imposing and impressive Ch&acirc;teau Couronneau comprises 38 hectares of vineyards, all certified for organic (Ecocert) and biodynamic (Demeter) wine production. The property itself lies just outside the small town of Ligueux to the south&nbsp;of Sainte-Foy-la-Grande and the Dordogne river. Located at the highest point in the local area at some 180 metres above sea-level, vines benefit from the clay/limestone soils with their ability to balance water retention with good drainage. The current owners, Christophe and B&eacute;n&eacute;dicte Piat&nbsp;purchased the property back in 1994 with the intention of restoring the ch&acirc;teau to its former glory and to re-plant the vineyards and&nbsp; convert to organics. The organic certification was acheived in 1999 and by 2011 all vineyards were being cultivated according to biodynamic principles. Of the total vineyard holdings, 35 hectares are planted to Merlot and just 3 hectares to Sauvignon Blanc and Sauvignon Gris.</span></p>', '<p>We deliver throughout New Zealand and to some locations overseas. Our deliveries are made by ourselves and trusted third party couriers. For further details on prices and delivery options please go to DELIVERY section of our website.</p>', 'Dark, spicy and fleshy. Nothing of the brittle charm of other wines without sulphur additive, but very juicy with a long finish. Immensely concentrated, with impressive plum and cherry fruit and solid structure. Matches dark meat and spicy sauces\r\nNo sulphites were added in the vineyard or in the cellar.', '<p><span style=\"color: #606060; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333px;\">Originally established way back in the 15th century, the imposing and impressive Ch&acirc;teau Couronneau comprises 38 hectares of vineyards, all certified for organic (Ecocert) and biodynamic (Demeter) wine production. The property itself lies just outside the small town of Ligueux to the south&nbsp;of Sainte-Foy-la-Grande and the Dordogne river. Located at the highest point in the local area at some 180 metres above sea-level, vines benefit from the clay/limestone soils with their ability to balance water retention with good drainage. The current owners, Christophe and B&eacute;n&eacute;dicte Piat&nbsp;purchased the property back in 1994 with the intention of restoring the ch&acirc;teau to its former glory and to re-plant the vineyards and&nbsp; convert to organics. The organic certification was acheived in 1999 and by 2011 all vineyards were being cultivated according to biodynamic principles. Of the total vineyard holdings, 35 hectares are planted to Merlot and just 3 hectares to Sauvignon Blanc and Sauvignon Gris.</span></p>', '<p>We deliver throughout New Zealand and to some locations overseas. Our deliveries are made by ourselves and trusted third party couriers. For further details on prices and delivery options please go to DELIVERY section of our website.</p>', 1, '', '2020-02-26 23:24:30', '2020-08-13 19:56:09'),
