('oLao1603768652OIpL', 'file-manager/wine/wine bottles/TKN Pinot_Rose_2019.jpg', '', '', 'Te Kano Estate Pinot Rose 2019', 'Te Kano Estate Pinot Rose 2019', 26, '', 750, 14, 1, 6, 4, 3, 'NZ', 9, 1, '[\"3\",\"5\",\"7\",\"10\",\"13\"]', NULL, NULL, 6, '2020-10-27', NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'Pale salmon in colour, this dry Rose shows aromas of pink grapefruit, watermelon and peach. An initial burst of fresh watermelon and raspberry leads into a crunchy medley of pink grapefruit,  red  apple  and passionfruit. A tightly poised, powerful and zesty rose, finishing fresh, dry and finely textured.', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">&lsquo;Te Kano&rsquo; means &lsquo;the seed&rsquo; in Maori, the name celebrates a prehistoric plant called Kowhai tree affectionately known as &lsquo;Old Man Kowhai&rsquo; on the Northburn slopes above Lake Dunstan where Te Kano Estate is located.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Te Kano Estate comprises three vineyards, Northburn, &lsquo;Jerome&rsquo; in Bannockburn and &lsquo;Eliza&rsquo; in Bannockburn. Te Kano Estate is always after the very best expression of site and climate which is called &lsquo;Terroir&rsquo; . A hand selection from vineyards and barrels is a must as what they emphasize is always the Quality, not the Quantity.</span></p>', '<p>We deliver throughout New Zealand and to some locations overseas. Our deliveries are made by ourselves and trusted third party couriers. For further details on prices and delivery options please go to DELIVERY section of our website.</p>', 'Pale salmon in colour, this dry Rose shows aromas of pink grapefruit, watermelon and peach. An initial burst of fresh watermelon and raspberry leads into a crunchy medley of pink grapefruit,  red  apple  and passionfruit. A tightly poised, powerful and zesty rose, finishing fresh, dry and finely textured.', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">&lsquo;Te Kano&rsquo; means &lsquo;the seed&rsquo; in Maori, the name celebrates a prehistoric plant called Kowhai tree affectionately known as &lsquo;Old Man Kowhai&rsquo; on the Northburn slopes above Lake Dunstan where Te Kano Estate is located.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-NZ\">Te Kano Estate comprises three vineyards, Northburn, &lsquo;Jerome&rsquo; in Bannockburn and &lsquo;Eliza&rsquo; in Bannockburn. Te Kano Estate is always after the very best expression of site and climate which is called &lsquo;Terroir&rsquo; . A hand selection from vineyards and barrels is a must as what they emphasize is always the Quality, not the Quantity.</span></p>', '<p>We deliver throughout New Zealand and to some locations overseas. Our deliveries are made by ourselves and trusted third party couriers. For further details on prices and delivery options please go to DELIVERY section of our website.</p>', 1, '', '2020-10-27 11:17:32', '2020-10-27 11:17:32'),
('OoOa1582730674twQM', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LVCA Le Charmant 2017', NULL, 268, '', 750, 13.5, 1, 1, 32, 1, 'NZ', 2, 2, '[9,8,7]', NULL, NULL, 12, '2020-02-26', '2021-02-26', 0, 113, 1, 0, 0, 'TBC', 'TBC', 'We deliver throughout New Zealand and to some locations overseas. Our deliveries are made by ourselves and trusted third party couriers. For further details on prices and delivery options please go to DELIVERY section of our website.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '2020-02-26 23:24:34', '2020-02-26 23:24:34'),
('orhA1582730675efmE', 'file-manager/wine/rippon.png', '', '', 'Rippon Nature Vine Pinot Noir 2016', 'Rippon Nature Vine Pinot Noir 2016', 66, '', 750, 13, 1, 1, 4, 1, 'NZ', 9, 2, '[\"5\",\"8\",\"9\"]', NULL, NULL, 12, '2020-02-26', '2021-02-26', 0, 156, 1, 0, 0, '另一片土地的农场声音：Rippon。 在瓦纳卡湖罗伊湾西侧，立邦的北向悬崖形成了终生的芒rain和粗砾石的交汇点，全部以片岩为基础，该地区最早种植了一些葡萄藤。 Rippon是从该土地上生长的所有成熟黑比诺葡萄酿制的葡萄酒。', '<p>葡萄</p>\r\n<p>黑比诺</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>起源</p>\r\n<p>Rippon的故事始于1912年，当时Percy Sargood爵士在瓦纳卡湖西侧购买了一个高乡村车站。三十年后，珀西（Percy）的孙子罗尔夫&middot;米尔斯（Rolfe Mills）在第二次世界大战中担任潜艇中尉时，被杜罗河谷片岩山坡上生长的葡萄树震惊，使他想起了瓦纳卡（Wanaka）的那些人。直觉出生。 1975年，罗尔夫（Rolfe）和他的妻子路易斯（Lois）开始种植实验性葡萄树，并于1982年开始商业种植15公顷的葡萄树，如今已包括了力宝（Rippon）。生物动力耕种，野生发酵，无需灌溉以及中奥塔哥地区最古老的藤本植物都可以帮助生产出适合其所在地的水果和葡萄酒。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>评论家怎么说</p>\r\n<p>95/100 Cameron Douglas MS（2016年份）</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;非常年轻的黑比诺葡萄酒，带有香料和泥土的香气和香味，红色水果和压碎的花朵，茶和老玫瑰。在口感上同样年轻，充满活力和充满活力的风味-碎石，暗红色浆果，橡木香料和轻度的烟味，有机的和冒险性的；干燥而冗长的，可口的，干燥的药草，带有红色浆果香的味道；单宁和酸味的年轻人味；可口的葡萄酒，但也很年轻。在2021年之前。最好在2022年到2032年之间饮用。&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>18/20 JancisRobinson.com，朱莉娅&middot;哈丁（Julia Harding）（2016年）</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;明亮的樱桃红色。微妙的岩石/矿物香气和大量尘土飞扬的暗红色水果。野生草药但没有百里香。太香了。在味觉上，岩石暗红色的水果完美地反映出来。非常细腻的质地。再次品尝在两个2014年份之后，单宁看起来更精致，更单宁柔顺，非常优雅和精致； Tinker\'s Block的质量更大但更优雅；在Diam之下&ndash;只有他们的Osteiner密封在螺帽下。这款酒能给人&ldquo;最完整的农场印象&rdquo;。每个葡萄块成熟的葡萄藤。葡萄块分开发酵，第一个冬天在桶中发酵。整捆葡萄占25-40％。（JH）。&rdquo;</p>', '<p>我们在整个新西兰以及海外一些地区提供服务。 我们的送货是由我们自己和值得信赖的第三方快递员完成的。 有关价格和送货方式的更多详细信息，请转到我们网站的&ldquo;送货&rdquo;部分。</p>', 'The farm voice of a distinct parcel of land: Rippon. On the western board of Roy’s Bay, Lake Wanaka, Rippon’s north-facing escarpment forms the meeting point of terminal moraines and coarse gravels, all based in schist, on which some of the region’s earliest vines were planted. Rippon is a Wine issued from all of the fully developed Pinot Noir vines growing in this land.', '<p>Grape</p>\r\n<p>Pinot Noir</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Its Origins</p>\r\n<p>Rippon\'s story begins in 1912 when Sir Percy Sargood bought a high country station on the western flanks of Lake Wanaka. Three decades later, while serving in the Second World War as a submarine lieutenant, Percy\'s grandson, Rolfe Mills, was struck by the vines growing on the schist slopes of the Douro Valley that reminded him of those back in Wanaka and, with that, a hunch was born. In 1975, Rolfe and his wife Lois began planting experimental vines and, in 1982 began the commercial planting of the 15ha that today comprise Rippon. Biodynamic farming, wild ferments, no irrigation and some of Central Otago&rsquo;s oldest vines on their own roots all help to produce fruit and wines which are true to their place.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>What The Critics Say</p>\r\n<p>95/100 Cameron Douglas MS (2016 vintage)</p>\r\n<p>\"Extremely youthful bouquet of Pinot Noir with aromas and scents of spice and earth, red fruits and crushed flowers, tea and old rose. Equally youthful on the palate with a vibrant and energy filled flavour profile - crushed rocks, dark red berry fruits, oak spice and whispers of smoke, organic and adventurous. Dry and lengthy, savoury, dried herb offset with a core of red berry fruit flavours. Youthful textures from tannins and acidity. A delicious wine but also a very young wine. Decant for service if opened before 2021. Best drinking 2022 through 2032.\"</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>18/20 JancisRobinson.com, Julia Harding (2016 vintage)</p>\r\n<p>\"Bright cherry red. Delicate rocky/mineral aroma and plenty of dusty dark-red fruit. Wild herbs but not thyme. So fragrant. On the palate, that rocky dark-red fruit perfectly mirrored. Very fine texture. Coming back to taste this again after the two single-block 2014s, this seems a little more delicate. The tannins finer and more supple. Very elegant and refined. Tinker&rsquo;s Block has more mass but this has more elegance. Under Diam &ndash; only their Osteiner is sealed under screwcap. This wine gives &lsquo;the most complete picture of the farm&rsquo;. Mature vines from each block. Blocks fermented separately and first winter in barrel. 25&ndash;40% whole bunch. (JH).\"</p>', '<p>We deliver throughout New Zealand and to some locations overseas. Our deliveries are made by ourselves and trusted third party couriers. For further details on prices and delivery options please go to DELIVERY section of our website.</p>', 1, '', '2020-02-26 23:24:35', '2020-10-21 12:44:14'),
