('rElq1582730677abCp', 'file-manager/wine/EI Candado.png', '', '', 'Valdespino \"EL Candado\" Pedro Ximenez NV', 'Valdespino \"EL Candado\" Pedro Ximenez NV', 26, '', 375, 17, 2, 3, 42, 2, 'ES', 37, 1, '[\"6\",\"7\",\"10\",\"13\"]', NULL, NULL, 12, '2020-02-26', '2021-02-26', 0, 193, 1, 0, 0, 'El Candado是西班牙人的挂锁，实际上每个瓶子都配有一个小挂锁和两个小钥匙。', '<p>El Candado是西班牙人的挂锁，实际上每个瓶子都配有一个小挂锁和两个小钥匙。当时的想法是，由于瓦尔德斯皮诺家族的某个人想把酒留给自己，所以这种茄子的屁股曾经被锁起来。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>像曼萨尼利亚德利西奥萨（Manzanilla Deliciosa）一样，坎大（El Candado）的鞋底曾经属于1972年瓦尔迪斯皮诺（Valdespino）接管的Almacenista Manuel deArg&uuml;eso。这是一个相当简单的鞋底，分为四个阶段。瓶装葡萄酒已有8年的历史，每升含糖约420克。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>嗅觉：嗅觉明亮，有很多葡萄干和无花果，但果味浓而不腻。蜂蜜和大量的木瓜冻。一些绿色，多叶的音符，以及淡淡的木质味。淡肉桂。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>味觉：非常甜美，曲折，但不能超过顶部。太妃糖笔记，无花果和蜂蜜甜点。番石榴接近尾端时会稍微变暗，并加入一些土耳其咖啡，深色焦糖和浅辣边缘（胡椒，豆蔻）。长时间完成。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>可用性：比其他PX困难一点。也存在于半瓶中。如果找不到，请查看例如威士忌交易所，它们在全球范围内发货。</p>', '<p>我们在整个新西兰以及海外一些地区提供服务。 我们的送货是由我们自己和值得信赖的第三方快递员完成的。 有关价格和送货方式的更多详细信息，请转到我们网站的&ldquo;送货&rdquo;部分。</p>', 'El Candado is Spanish for the padlock, and indeed every bottle comes with a small padlock and two little keys.', '<p style=\"line-height: 24px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; color: #333333; font-size: 1.13em; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #222222 !important;\">El Candado</span>&nbsp;is Spanish for&nbsp;<em>the padlock</em>, and indeed every bottle comes with a small padlock and two little keys. The idea is that butt from this solera used to be locked away as someone from the&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #222222; transition: all 0.8s ease-in-out 0s; font-weight: bold;\" href=\"https://www.sherrynotes.com/2014/bodegas/valdespino/\">Valdespino&nbsp;</a>family wanted to keep the wine to himself.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 24px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; color: #333333; font-size: 1.13em; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif;\">Like the Manzanilla Deliciosa, the&nbsp;solera for El Candado used to belong to the&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #222222; transition: all 0.8s ease-in-out 0s; font-weight: bold;\" href=\"https://www.sherrynotes.com/2014/background/almacenistas/\">almacenista</a>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #222222 !important;\">Manuel de Arg&uuml;eso</span>&nbsp;which was taken over by Valdespino in 1972. It is a fairly simple solera of four stages. The bottled wine is around 8 years old and contains around 420 grams of sugar per liter.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 24px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; color: #333333; font-size: 1.13em; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #222222 !important;\">N</span><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #222222 !important;\">ose:&nbsp;</span>quite a bright nose, with lots of raisins and figs but in a fruity way rather than the sticky way. Honey and plenty of quince jelly. Some green, leafy notes too, as well as a light woody touch. Light cinnamon.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 24px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; color: #333333; font-size: 1.13em; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #222222 !important;\">Mouth:&nbsp;</span>very sweet and unctuous, but again not over the top. Toffee notes, desserts with figs and honey. Guava. Grows slightly darker towards the end, with some Turkish coffee, dark caramel, and a light spicy edge (pepper, cardamom). Long finish.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 24px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; color: #333333; font-size: 1.13em; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #222222 !important;\">Availability:&nbsp;</span>a bit more difficult than other PXs. Also exists in half bottles. If you can&rsquo;t find it, check&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #222222; transition: all 0.8s ease-in-out 0s; font-weight: bold;\" href=\"https://www.thewhiskyexchange.com/aff/4431885/aff/4431885/p/33969/valdespino-pedro-ximenez-el-candado\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">The Whisky Exchange</a>&nbsp;for instance, they ship around the world.</p>', '<p>We deliver throughout New Zealand and to some locations overseas. Our deliveries are made by ourselves and trusted third party couriers. For further details on prices and delivery options please go to DELIVERY section of our website.</p>', 1, '', '2020-02-26 23:24:37', '2020-10-19 18:00:42'),
