INSERT INTO `wine_basic_category` (`Category`, `Description`, `DescriptionEn`, `Image`, `updated_at`) VALUES
('reds', '賦予顏色和風味的不是肉，而是葡萄的皮。因此，有些飲酒者覺得紅色更“令人滿意”-僅僅是因為他們有更多的風味來源！白人的果肉具有蘋果/柑橘的味道，而紅色和黑色的水果則具有紅色的“果味”，而浸漬（在皮膚上浸泡/發酵）則具有辛辣和泥土的味道。這種“浸出”幾乎是紅色所獨有的，也導致了更飽滿的質地和固體（酚醛樹脂）的重量。除顏色化合物外，最重要的酚類是單寧酸。單寧的品質無論從皮和果皮中都可以幫助其成熟，並確定其樣式為柔和果味（低單寧）或堅挺而結構化（高單寧）。', 'It is not the flesh but the skin of the grape that gives colour - and flavour. Hence some drinkers find reds more ‘satisfying’ - simply because they have more flavour sources! While whites have apple/citrus flavours of pulp, these are ‘built over’ in reds by stronger red and black fruit, spicy and earthy flavours caused by maceration (soaking/fermenting on skins). This ‘leaching’ is almost exclusive to reds, also leading to fuller texture and weight of solids (phenolics). The most important phenolics - besides colour compounds - are tannins. From both skin and pip, the quality of tannins help red wines to age and determines their style as soft and fruity (low tannin) or firm and structured (high tannin).', 'file-manager\\wine\\pinot-noir.jpg', '2020-04-11 15:49:52'),
('sparklings', '起泡酒是經典的慶祝活動，但泡沫加上新鮮感使它成為任何一天的開胃酒。大多數起泡酒都是由白葡萄製成，並遵循兩種原型。最著名的是香檳-如果在其他地方製作，則稱為“ Methode Traditionelle”-在瓶中進行第二次發酵會產生二氧化碳氣泡和復雜的酵母菌。另一個是意大利的普羅塞克（Prosecco），在此之前，先對可飲用的葡萄酒進行加壓，然後再裝瓶，以使泡沫更加多汁。像Moscato d\'Asti一樣，煙火也可以很甜，或者像意大利的Lambrusco或澳大利亞的起泡酒設拉子（Shiraz）一樣，也可以是紅色。', 'Sparkling wine is a classic celebration, but fizz plus freshness makes a great any-day aperitif. Most sparkling wines are made from white grapes and follow two archetypes. The most famous is Champagne - called ‘Methode Traditionelle’ if made elsewhere - in which a second fermentation in bottle produces carbon dioxide bubbles and yeasty complexity. The other is Italian Prosecco, in which drink-young wines are pressurised before bottling to add fizz to more juicy fruit flavours. Sparklers can also be sweet like Moscato d’Asti, or red like Italy’s Lambrusco or Australia’s richer sparkling Shiraz.', 'file-manager\\wine\\champagne_2.jpg', '2020-04-11 15:54:40'),
('whites', '白葡萄酒的酒體清淡，酸度更明顯，使其成為開胃酒或搭配白肉和魚類菜餚。白葡萄酒是由任何葡萄的半透明果肉和果汁製成的-無論是白葡萄酒還是紅皮膚。通常情況下，綠色或粉紅色皮膚的水果會製成檸檬色或稻草色的葡萄酒，但黑皮諾（Pinot Noir）之類的紅葡萄果肉也可能無法與皮膚接觸，從而製成“草莓金色”的白葡萄酒，稱為Vin Gris或Blanc de Noir。儘管法國人的當地人喝酒的時間只有21％，但他們仍然是法國人中最偉大，最耀眼的白人。新西蘭以長相思（Sauvignon Blanc）而聞名，我們是白葡萄酒的第三大消費者，佔56％。令人驚訝的是，世界上最大的白人飲酒者是澳大利亞人，佔60％！嗯，我想知道他們在喝誰？', 'Whites wines are lighter-bodied with more obvious acidity, making them good aperitifs or with white meat and fish dishes. Whites are the made from the translucent flesh and juice of any grape - whether white or even red-skinned. Commonly green or pink-skinned fruit make lemon or straw-coloured wines but the pulp of a red grape like Pinot Noir can also be denied skin contact to make ‘strawberry blond’ whites called Vin Gris or Blanc de Noir. The greatest still and sparkling whites are French, though their locals only drink them 21 percent of the time. New Zealand is famous for Sauvignon Blanc and we are third highest white wine consumers at 56 percent. Surprisingly, the world’s biggest white drinkers are Australians at 60 percent! Hmmm, I wonder whose they are drinking?', 'file-manager\\wine\\sauvignon-blanc_1.jpg', '2020-04-11 15:54:05');

